Vertical sum of firing rates is the same, that's why the vertical generation of spike counts doesn't make sense at all
I suppose the vertical firing rate sum is almost the same for every position, bc the positions are continuous
Consequentially, the sum of spikes (generated vertically) will always be the same
Also the spike vectors are completely the same so this cannot be the right approach

DECODING POSITIONS¶

Indices = time points
Time window for counting spikes is 5 (so I take FIRST 5 succesive points for generating a FIRST count vector)

sc_time_step
Out[ ]:
5
In [ ]:
# !! num_positions must be dividible w/ sc_time_step bc of reshaping the original_positions
num_time_windows = math.ceil(num_positions/sc_time_step)
spike_counts = np.zeros((num_time_windows, num_neurons))
fr_sums = np.zeros((num_time_windows, num_neurons))
decoded_positions = np.zeros(num_time_windows)
tw_original_positions = circ_positions.reshape(num_time_windows, -1)
In [ ]:
for time_window in range(num_time_windows):
    for neuron in range(num_neurons):                                       # sliding through the positions
        fr_sums[time_window][neuron] = sum(firing_rates_cp[neuron][ time_window*sc_time_step : (time_window+1)*sc_time_step] )
        proba = np.random.random()
        spike_counts[time_window][neuron] = poisson.rvs(fr_sums[time_window][neuron], sc_time_step) if proba > dropout else 0

Pipline for every decoding approach

  1. approach_name
  2. for time_window: decoded_positions[time_window] = approach_algorithm(spike_counts[time_window])
  3. test_decoded_pos_rnd_index(tw_original_positions, decoded_positions, approach_name:str)
  4. mse, square_diff = MSE_decoded_original_pos(decoded_positions, original_positions)
  5. plt_square_diff(mse, squared_diff, approach_name:str, skip_ticks_step=10)
  6. plot_spike_count_statistics_vs_squared_diff(mse, squared_diff, approach_name:str, skip_ticks_step=10) / plt_scatter_sqd_sc(spike_counts, squared_diff)
  7. plt_circular_distance(decoded_positions, tw_original_positions, approach_name:str, skip_ticks_step=10)
  8. plt_real_vs_decoded_trajectory(decoded_positions, tw_original_positions, approach_name, sc_time_step=sc_time_step)
  9. plt_decoded_positions(tw_original_positions, decoded_positions, circ_positions, sc_time_step, num_time_windows_limit, tw_bounds:bool, approach_name:str)
